*******************************************************************************
disp3Dmap 	    -  Display maps from 3D gradient shimming.
*******************************************************************************

This document does not describe the operation and utility of the 3D gradient shim
maps. See the 3D Gradient Shimming User Guide. This document only describes how to
control the colors used to display the maps.

From the Edit menu, select "Display Options...". Across the top of this popup,
there are radio buttons labeled UI, Display, and Plot. Select the Display radio button.
You are then presented with four Tabs. Select the Canvas tab. The "Spectrum 8" color
controls the border and circle. The "Spectrum 9" color controls the lattice. The
"FID envelope" color controls the scale bar. The colors "Spectrum 2" to Spectrum 7"
color the rotating colors of the map data. To control the color of the text information,
go to the Annotation tab. The Fields item in the Parameters group controls the text.
